00:14:34,209 --> 00:14:39,430
President Joe Biden: Look, my intention as I said to begin with is that I would run again.

234
00:14:39,430 --> 00:14:41,170
But it's just an intention.

235
00:14:41,170 --> 00:14:44,220
But is it a firm decision that I run again?

236
00:14:44,220 --> 00:14:45,569
That remains to be seen.

237
00:14:45,569 --> 00:14:50,329
Scott Pelley: Mr. President, you are the oldest president ever.

238
00:14:50,329 --> 00:14:51,779
President Joe Biden: Pretty good shape, huh?

239
00:14:51,779 --> 00:14:54,369
Scott Pelley: Which leads to my next question.

240
00:14:54,369 --> 00:14:57,790
You are more aware of this than anyone.

241
00:14:57,790 --> 00:15:01,600
Some people ask whether you are fit for the job.

242
00:15:01,600 --> 00:15:04,589
And when you hear that, I wonder what you think.

243
00:15:04,589 --> 00:15:07,110
President Joe Biden: Watch me.

244
00:15:07,110 --> 00:15:10,709
And ma-- honest to God, that's all I think.

245
00:15:10,709 --> 00:15:12,079
Watch me.

246
00:15:12,079 --> 00:15:17,170
If you think I don't have the energy level or the mental acuity, then-- then, you know,

247
00:15:17,170 --> 00:15:18,429
that's one thing.

248
00:15:18,429 --> 00:15:22,100
It's another thing, you just watch and-- and, you know, keep my schedule.

249
00:15:22,100 --> 00:15:23,689
Do what I'm doing.

250
00:15:23,689 --> 00:15:28,959
I-- I think that-- you know-- I don't-- when I sit down with our NATO allies and keep 'em

251
00:15:28,959 --> 00:15:30,949
together, I don't have 'em saying, "Wait a minute, w-- how-- how old are you?

252
00:15:30,949 --> 00:15:31,949
What are you-- what say?"

253
00:15:31,949 --> 00:15:38,009
You know, I mean, it's a matter of, you know, that old expression: The proof of the pudding's

254
00:15:38,009 --> 00:15:39,009
in the eating.

255
00:15:39,009 --> 00:15:44,259
I mean, I-- I-- I respect the fact that people would say, you know, "You're old."

256
00:15:44,259 --> 00:15:50,250
And-- but I think it relates to h-- how much energy you have, and whether or not the job

257
00:15:50,250 --> 00:15:55,059
you're doing is one consistent with what any person of any age would be able to do.

258
00:15:55,059 --> 00:15:57,859
Scott Pelley: How would you say your mental focus is?

259
00:15:57,859 --> 00:16:00,410
President Joe Biden: Oh, it's focused.

260
00:16:00,410 --> 00:16:07,149
I'd say it's-- I think it's-- I-- I haven't-- look, I have trouble even mentioning, even

261
00:16:07,149 --> 00:16:09,980
saying to myself, my own head, the number of years.

262
00:16:09,980 --> 00:16:13,179
I no more think of myself as being as old as I am than fly.

263
00:16:13,179 --> 00:16:20,879
I mean, it's just not-- I haven't-- observed anything in terms of-- there's not things

264
00:16:20,879 --> 00:16:25,869
I don't do now that I did before, whether it's physical, or mental, or anything else.

265
00:16:25,869 --> 00:16:31,029
Scott Pelley: You have had a string of legislative successes recently.

266
00:16:31,029 --> 00:16:33,939
President Joe Biden: How'd an old guy do that?

267
00:16:33,939 --> 00:16:42,109
Scott Pelley: But your approval rating in the country is well below 50%.

268
00:16:42,109 --> 00:16:43,779
And I wonder why you think that is.

269
00:16:43,779 --> 00:16:46,029
President Joe Biden: This is a really difficult time.

270
00:16:46,029 --> 00:16:50,649
We're at an inflection point in the history of this country.

271
00:16:50,649 --> 00:16:54,239
We're gonna make decisions, and we're making decisions now, that are gonna determine what

272
00:16:54,239 --> 00:16:57,160
we're gonna look like the next ten years from now.

273
00:16:57,160 --> 00:17:05,050
I think you'd agree that the impact on the psyche of the American people as a consequence

274
00:17:05,050 --> 00:17:08,690
of the pandemic is profound.

275
00:17:08,690 --> 00:17:10,880
Think of how that has changed everything.

276
00:17:10,880 --> 00:17:15,770
You know, people's attitudes about themselves, their families, about the state of the nation,

277
00:17:15,770 --> 00:17:18,019
about the state of their communities.

278
00:17:18,019 --> 00:17:22,250
And so there's a lot of uncertainty out there, a great deal of uncertainty.

279
00:17:22,250 --> 00:17:24,380
And we lost a million people.

280
00:17:24,380 --> 00:17:27,660
A million people to COVID.

281
00:17:27,660 --> 00:17:31,919
When I got in office, when I-- I got elected, only 2 million people had been vaccinated.

282
00:17:31,919 --> 00:17:35,980
I got 220 million-- m-- my point is it takes time.

283
00:17:35,980 --> 00:17:39,169
We were left in a very difficult situation.

284
00:17:39,169 --> 00:17:42,320
it's been a very difficult time.

285
00:17:42,320 --> 00:17:44,220
Very difficult.

286
00:17:44,220 --> 00:17:47,860
And a difficult life for the president.

287
00:17:47,860 --> 00:17:52,510
In 1972 he lost his wife and daughter in a car accident.

288
00:17:52,510 --> 00:17:57,980
He lost his son, Beau, to cancer in 2015 at the age of 46.

289
00:17:57,980 --> 00:18:02,510
And his son, Hunter, has been a lightning rod for suspicion.

290
00:18:02,510 --> 00:18:10,000
Hunter Biden's former addiction to crack cocaine led to a life he describes as "non-stop depravity."

291
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:14,710
He has also acknowledged a federal investigation into his taxes.

292
00:18:14,710 --> 00:18:20,889
Congress investigated Hunter Biden's job with a Ukrainian company at the time that his father

293
00:18:20,889 --> 00:18:24,900
ran Ukrainian policy in the Obama administration.

294
00:18:24,900 --> 00:18:31,269
A Republican investigation, however, uncovered no wrongdoing by then-Vice President Biden.

295
00:18:31,269 --> 00:18:38,510
Scott Pelley: Mr. President, if you run again, Republicans are most likely to go after your

296
00:18:38,510 --> 00:18:42,169
son Hunter once again.

297
00:18:42,169 --> 00:18:50,100
And I wonder what you would like to say about your son and whether any of his troubles have

298
00:18:50,100 --> 00:18:54,269
caused conflicts for you or for the United States.

299
00:18:54,269 --> 00:18:58,539
President Joe Biden: I love my son, number one.

300
00:18:58,539 --> 00:19:02,179
He fought-- an addiction problem.

301
00:19:02,179 --> 00:19:03,179
He overcame it.

302
00:19:03,179 --> 00:19:04,550
He wrote about it.

303
00:19:04,550 --> 00:19:11,100
And no, there's not a single thing that I've observed at all from th-- that would affect

304
00:19:11,100 --> 00:19:15,990
me or the United States relative to my son Hunter.

305
00:19:15,990 --> 00:19:20,909
Republican investigations are likely to resume if Mr. Biden loses either the House or the

306
00:19:20,909 --> 00:19:26,640
Senate, and history shows that presidents usually lose seats in Congress in a midterm

307
00:19:26,640 --> 00:19:28,080
election.

308
00:19:28,080 --> 00:19:33,360
If so, the president's remaining ambitions may be beyond his reach.

309
00:19:33,360 --> 00:19:37,720
President Joe Biden: For example, we passed the most extensive gun legislation in 30 years,

310
00:19:37,720 --> 00:19:41,899
although I'm not gonna rest till we get assault weapons banned, which I did once before when

311
00:19:41,899 --> 00:19:42,899
I was a senator.

312
00:19:42,899 --> 00:19:43,899
Scott Pelley: Assault weapons banned?

313
00:19:43,899 --> 00:19:45,809
President Joe Biden: Assault-- assault weapons banned.

314
00:19:45,809 --> 00:19:48,510
There's no rationale.

315
00:19:48,510 --> 00:19:51,190
Deer aren't running through the woods wearing Kevlar vests.

316
00:19:51,190 --> 00:19:58,900
Scott Pelley: Somebody came in and told you about Uvalde when it happened, and I wonder

317
00:19:58,900 --> 00:19:59,970
what you thought.

318
00:19:59,970 --> 00:20:04,509
President Joe Biden: Again, I've gone to every one of those places.

319
00:20:04,509 --> 00:20:10,120
And in Uvalde, I spent time with every sing-- four hours.

320
00:20:10,120 --> 00:20:18,290
Four hours in the pain, pain, and it's just so, so unnecessary.

321
00:20:18,290 --> 00:20:20,650
So wrong.

322
00:20:20,650 --> 00:20:24,350
Who the hell m-- (SIGH) don't get me going.

323
00:20:24,350 --> 00:20:30,360
But I met with every one of those families and i-- and-- and the extended families for

324
00:20:30,360 --> 00:20:31,990
four hours.

325
00:20:31,990 --> 00:20:36,870
look, our kids should be learning how to read and write, not duck and cover.

326
00:20:36,870 --> 00:20:38,179
Think about that.

327
00:20:38,179 --> 00:20:41,350
Think of the mental impact on these kids going back to school.

328
00:20:41,350 --> 00:20:43,250
We saw it.

329
00:20:43,250 --> 00:20:44,510
It's wrong.

330
00:20:44,510 --> 00:20:45,779
It's wrong.

331
00:20:45,779 --> 00:20:47,390
It's not who we are.

332
00:20:47,390 --> 00:20:49,960
And we've gotta stop it.

333
00:20:49,960 --> 00:20:51,669
We've got to stop it.

334
00:20:51,669 --> 00:20:59,669
And the NRA continuing to push the sale of-- assault and semiautomatic weapons is bizarre.

335
00:20:59,669 --> 00:21:05,639
The much more modest bi-partisan gun law that passed this summer may be the best example

336
00:21:05,639 --> 00:21:09,960
of the president's legislative breakthroughs that no one thought possible.

337
00:21:09,960 --> 00:21:12,139
"How'd an old guy do that?"

338
00:21:12,139 --> 00:21:13,850
He asked us earlier.

339
00:21:13,850 --> 00:21:15,490
We have a theory.

340
00:21:15,490 --> 00:21:20,570
Joe Biden is among the longest-serving politicians in Washington.

341
00:21:20,570 --> 00:21:26,360
If there is less bounce in the step than there once was, if the words don't flow like they

342
00:21:26,360 --> 00:21:34,100
used to, maybe there's something to be said for knowhowâ€”five decades on the Hill and

343
00:21:34,100 --> 00:21:35,100
in the Oval.

344
00:21:35,100 --> 00:21:41,669
Scott Pelley: Concerning politics, Mr. President, you were elected to the Senate in 1972.

345
00:21:41,669 --> 00:21:42,860
You were 29 years old.

346
00:21:42,860 --> 00:21:53,730
And in those days, it seemed that the parties worked together to move the country forward.

347
00:21:53,730 --> 00:22:00,299
And I think many Americans feel that that no longer happens, and, in fact, may be impossible

348
00:22:00,299 --> 00:22:01,299
now.

349
00:22:01,299 --> 00:22:02,750
President Joe Biden: Well, I don't think it's impossible.

350
00:22:02,750 --> 00:22:04,669
But it-- it-- it's changed.

351
00:22:04,669 --> 00:22:08,580
What we do today, think about it, it's all personal attacks.

352
00:22:08,580 --> 00:22:09,809
It's about motive.

353
00:22:09,809 --> 00:22:13,860
It's not about, "I disagree with you on the-- on the subject matter.

354
00:22:13,860 --> 00:22:21,659
And secondly, I think that-- it's-- I think it's fair to say that we've not had a president

355
00:22:21,659 --> 00:22:26,130
like the last president, who has made all of it so personal.

356
00:22:26,130 --> 00:22:31,321
I've had six Republican senators, I promised I'd never say their names and I won't, come

357
00:22:31,321 --> 00:22:35,779
up to me in the last two years and say, "Joe, I agree with you, but if I-- if I vote this

358
00:22:35,779 --> 00:22:37,909
way it's gonna-- they're gonna primary me.

359
00:22:37,909 --> 00:22:40,000
I'm gonna lose an election."

360
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:41,840
It didn't used to be that way.

361
00:22:41,840 --> 00:22:43,429
But it's coming back a little bit.

362
00:22:43,429 --> 00:22:44,429
It's coming back.

363
00:22:44,429 --> 00:22:45,500
Scott Pelley: Do you see it?

364
00:22:45,500 --> 00:22:50,529
It seems to me, Mr. President, that-- when you were-- first came to the Senate, the other

365
00:22:50,529 --> 00:22:55,929
guy had a bad idea, and now the other guy is a bad guy.

366
00:22:55,929 --> 00:22:58,620
And I don't know how you get back to that-- President Joe Biden: Well, I'll tell you what,

367
00:22:58,620 --> 00:22:59,840
think about this.

368
00:22:59,840 --> 00:23:06,850
I was able to get-- we were able to get a bipartisan $1.2 trillion package done for

369
00:23:06,850 --> 00:23:10,670
dealing with the whole question of rebuilding the country, the roads and the highways.

370
00:23:10,670 --> 00:23:14,269
the fact of the matter is we've gotten a lot of things done bipartisanly.

371
00:23:14,269 --> 00:23:20,460
And everybody said, "We're not gonna do anything, don't let Biden have any successes," et cetera.

372
00:23:20,460 --> 00:23:23,630
So it's still a way to go, but I think we're making some progress.

373
00:23:23,630 --> 00:23:29,669
Scott Pelley: You have lived a long life of triumph and tragedy.

374
00:23:29,669 --> 00:23:32,299
In November you'll be 80.

375
00:23:32,299 --> 00:23:36,480
And I wonder what it is that keeps you in the arena.

376
00:23:36,480 --> 00:23:41,800
President Joe Biden: Well, look-- I've had tragedies.

377
00:23:41,800 --> 00:23:48,870
I've lost part of my soul when I lost my son Beau, I lost my wife and my daughter in an

378
00:23:48,870 --> 00:23:49,870
accident.

379
00:23:49,870 --> 00:23:54,190
I think of all the people who've gone through what I've gone through and a lot more without

380
00:23:54,190 --> 00:23:55,190
what I had.

381
00:23:55,190 --> 00:23:57,830
I have had incredibly supportive family.

382
00:23:57,830 --> 00:24:03,130
There's so many, literally, heroes getting up every day putting one foot in front of

383
00:24:03,130 --> 00:24:10,910
the other with no help, I constantly think what would Beau want me to do?

384
00:24:10,910 --> 00:24:16,230
What would-- and, you know, this gets me a long way, this rosary.

385
00:24:16,230 --> 00:24:20,030
Catholic and devout, he keeps a rosary in his pocket.

386
00:24:20,030 --> 00:24:26,529
And he showed us his other inspiration in a cartoon that his father had framed.

387
00:24:26,529 --> 00:24:33,889
In it, the viking, Hagar, confronts God after a lighting strikeâ€”a blow like those endured

388
00:24:33,889 --> 00:24:34,889
by the president.

389
00:24:34,889 --> 00:24:37,379
President Joe Biden: And he's looking up, and what's he say?

390
00:24:37,379 --> 00:24:39,070
He says, "Why me, God?"

391
00:24:39,070 --> 00:24:40,960
And the next scene, a voice from heaven, "Why not?"

392
00:24:40,960 --> 00:24:41,960
That's my dad.

393
00:24:41,960 --> 00:24:42,960
"Why not, Joey?

394
00:24:42,960 --> 00:24:43,960
Why not you?

395
00:24:43,960 --> 00:24:49,150
Why not-- what makes you so different?

396
00:24:49,150 --> 00:24:50,559
Just get up."

397
00:24:50,559 --> 00:24:54,139
My mom's expression was, "Just get up.

398
00:24:54,139 --> 00:24:55,399
Get up.

399
00:24:55,399 --> 00:24:56,399
Get up."

400
00:24:56,399 --> 00:24:58,039
Scott Pelley: And you feel you have more to give.

401
00:24:58,039 --> 00:24:59,720
President Joe Biden: A lot more to give.

402
00:24:59,720 --> 00:25:00,769
A lot more to give.